context: Alaska is the northernmost and westernmost state in the United States and has the most easterly longitude in the United States because the <a3_0><b8_0>Aleutian Islands<b8_0/><a3_0/> extend into the eastern hemisphere. Alaska is the only non-contiguous U.S. state on continental North America; about <a2_0><b7_0>500<b7_0/><a2_0/> miles (800 km) of British Columbia (Canada) separates Alaska from Washington. It is technically part of the continental U.S., but is sometimes not included in colloquial use; Alaska is not part of the contiguous U.S., often called <a0_0>"<b4_0><b5_0>the Lower 48<b5_0/><b4_0/>"<a0_0/>. The capital city, <a1_0><b6_0>Juneau<b6_0/><a1_0/>, is situated on the mainland of the North American continent but is not connected by road to the rest of the North American highway system.
